---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import LegacyHeader from '../components/LegacyHeader.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import ContactSection from '../components/ContactSection.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import ButtonPrimary from '../components/ButtonPrimary.astro';
import ButtonSecondary from '../components/ButtonSecondary.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Technical SEO Services In The Philippines - Bright Forge SEO"
  description="Technical SEO services in the Philippines for crawlability, Core Web Vitals, indexation, migrations, structured data and site health fixes that protect rankings and leads."
  faqs={[
    { question: "What does technical SEO fix first?", answer: "We usually start with crawl access, indexation, Core Web Vitals, mobile rendering, broken internal links, redirect chains, duplicate pages, sitemap hygiene and schema issues. The priority is not the longest issue list; it is the fixes most likely to unlock rankings, traffic and enquiries." },
    { question: "Do we need technical SEO if the site already looks good?", answer: "Yes, because design quality and search accessibility are different things. A site can look polished while Google struggles with slow templates, blocked resources, duplicate URLs, weak internal links or JavaScript rendering problems." },
    { question: "Can you work with our developer?", answer: "Yes. We can diagnose the issues, write the implementation brief, QA the developer's changes and monitor Search Console after release so fixes do not create new ranking or conversion problems." },
    { question: "How quickly can technical SEO improve results?", answer: "Critical crawl and indexation fixes can show movement within weeks. Performance, architecture and migration work usually compounds over one to three months as Google recrawls the site and users get a faster path to enquiry." }
  ]}
>
  <LegacyHeader slot="header" />
  
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <Hero
    badgeIcon="fas fa-cogs"
    badgeText="Technical SEO Experts"
    title="Technical SEO Services In The Philippines"
    breadcrumbCurrent="Technical SEO Services Philippines"
  >
    <Fragment slot="story">
      <p>A site can look fine and still leak rankings through crawl waste, Core Web Vitals, indexation problems, duplicate URLs, weak internal links or JavaScript that search engines struggle to render. That is the work technical SEO is meant to catch before it quietly costs traffic.</p>
      <p>We audit the parts users do not see, then turn the findings into fixes developers can actually ship. The goal is a cleaner technical foundation, faster pages, better crawl access and less friction between search visibility and enquiries.</p>
    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="actions">
      <ButtonPrimary href="/contact/" text="Fix Your Technical Foundation" />
      <ButtonSecondary href="#services" text="View Our Services" />
    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="visual">
      <div class="hero-image-container">
        <div class="technical-icon-grid">
          <div class="tech-icon"><i class="fas fa-cogs"></i></div>
          <div class="tech-icon"><i class="fas fa-tachometer-alt"></i></div>
          <div class="tech-icon"><i class="fas fa-sitemap"></i></div>
          <div class="tech-icon"><i class="fas fa-mobile-alt"></i></div>
          <div class="tech-icon"><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i></div>
          <div class="tech-icon"><i class="fas fa-code"></i></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Fragment>
  </Hero>

  <!-- Why Technical SEO Section -->
  <section class="why-technical-section">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Why Technical SEO Is Usually the <span>Hidden Blocker</span></h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="content-explanation">
        <div class="content-card">
          <div class="content-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-cogs"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="content-text">
            <p>Content and backlinks cannot do their job if search engines are wasting crawl budget, landing on duplicate URLs, missing important pages or giving up on slow templates. Technical SEO makes the site easier to crawl, render, index and trust.</p>
            
            <p>We prioritise the fixes with commercial impact: pages that should be indexed, templates that are too slow, redirects that dilute signals, schema that needs tightening and internal links that should point authority towards the pages that sell.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Core Technical SEO Services Section -->
  <section id="services" class="services-section-new">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="services-layout">
        <div class="services-content">
          <h2>Our Core Technical SEO <span>Services</span></h2>

          <div class="service-list">
            <div class="service-item">
              <h3>Site Architecture Optimization</h3>
              <p>Streamline your URL structure, internal linking, site hierarchy, XML sitemaps, and robots.txt to help search engines crawl and understand your site efficiently.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="service-item">
              <h3>Performance Optimization</h3>
              <p>Improve page speed, Core Web Vitals, server response times, and resource delivery through minification, compression, and image optimization for better rankings and user experience.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="service-item">
              <h3>Mobile Optimization</h3>
              <p>Ensure mobile-first indexing compliance with responsive design, mobile usability fixes, proper touch element spacing, and lightning-fast mobile page speeds.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="service-item">
              <h3>Security & Indexing</h3>
              <p>Implement SSL, manage HTTPS migrations, configure security headers, and optimize crawl budgets to improve index coverage and protect your site's reputation.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="services-visual">
          <div class="visual-card">
            <div class="visual-icon">
              <i class="fas fa-cogs"></i>
            </div>
            <h3>Technical Priorities</h3>
            <p class="visual-stat">Fix first</p>
            <p class="visual-label">Crawl, speed, indexation, schema and conversion blockers</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Process Section -->
  <section class="process-section">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="process-header">
        <h2>Our Technical SEO <span>Process</span></h2>
        <p>We follow a systematic approach to identify, fix, and monitor your website's technical health.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="process-grid">
        <div class="process-box orange-bg">
          <div class="process-box-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-search"></i>
          </div>
          <h3>Technical Audit</h3>
          <p>We perform a comprehensive technical analysis of your website using advanced tools to identify all issues affecting your search performance.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="process-box white-bg">
          <div class="process-box-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-bullseye"></i>
          </div>
          <h3>Issue Prioritization</h3>
          <p>We categorize and prioritize technical issues based on their impact on your search rankings and user experience.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="process-box orange-bg">
          <div class="process-box-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-clipboard-list"></i>
          </div>
          <h3>Implementation Plan</h3>
          <p>We create a detailed roadmap for fixing technical issues, ensuring changes are made safely and effectively.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="process-box white-bg">
          <div class="process-box-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-bolt"></i>
          </div>
          <h3>Optimization Execution</h3>
          <p>Our team implements the necessary technical fixes and optimizations, carefully monitoring for any potential impacts.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="process-box orange-bg">
          <div class="process-box-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-vial"></i>
          </div>
          <h3>Testing & Validation</h3>
          <p>We thoroughly test all changes across different devices and browsers to ensure everything works perfectly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="process-box white-bg">
          <div class="process-box-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-chart-bar"></i>
          </div>
          <h3>Monitoring & Maintenance</h3>
          <p>We continuously monitor your website's technical health and performance, addressing new issues as they arise.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Benefits Section -->
  <section class="benefits-section">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="benefits-header">
        <h2>The Benefits of Strong <span>Technical SEO</span></h2>
        <p>Investing in technical SEO delivers lasting advantages for your website and business.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="benefits-layout">
        <div class="benefits-visual">
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1551434678-e076c223a692?w=800&q=80"
            alt="Professional team collaborating on technical SEO projects"
            class="benefits-image"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="benefits-grid">
          <div class="benefit-card">
            <div class="benefit-icon">
              <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i>
            </div>
            <h3>Improved Rankings</h3>
            <p>A technically optimized website has a better chance of ranking higher in search results, as search engines can easily crawl and understand your content.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="benefit-card">
            <div class="benefit-icon">
              <i class="fas fa-bolt"></i>
            </div>
            <h3>Faster Loading Times</h3>
            <p>Technical optimizations lead to faster page loading times, reducing bounce rates and improving user engagement.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="benefit-card">
            <div class="benefit-icon">
              <i class="fas fa-users"></i>
            </div>
            <h3>Better User Experience</h3>
            <p>A well-structured, fast-loading website provides a superior user experience, leading to higher conversion rates.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="benefit-card">
            <div class="benefit-icon">
              <i class="fas fa-mobile-alt"></i>
            </div>
            <h3>Mobile Excellence</h3>
            <p>Your website will perform flawlessly across all devices, capturing the growing mobile audience in the Philippines.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="commercial-proof-section">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="commercial-proof-layout">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">What we look for</p>
          <h2>Technical SEO questions businesses usually ask after rankings stall</h2>
          <p>We do not hand over a 70-page export and call it strategy. We isolate the issues that are most likely to affect visibility, leads and migration safety, then we give the developer or content team a practical fix path.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="proof-list">
          <li><strong>Can Google reach the right pages?</strong><span>Crawl paths, sitemaps, canonicals, redirects and robots rules.</span></li>
          <li><strong>Are templates costing conversions?</strong><span>Core Web Vitals, mobile layout, slow scripts and heavy media.</span></li>
          <li><strong>Is the site sending mixed signals?</strong><span>Duplicate content, thin pages, weak internal links and schema drift.</span></li>
          <li><strong>Will fixes survive release?</strong><span>QA checks, Search Console monitoring and post-launch crawl comparisons.</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section-commercial">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2>Technical SEO questions businesses usually ask</h2>
      <div class="faq-list-commercial">
        <article><h3>What does technical SEO fix first?</h3><p>We start with the blockers most likely to affect search visibility and enquiries: crawl access, indexation, Core Web Vitals, mobile rendering, broken links, redirect chains, duplicate pages, sitemap hygiene and schema issues.</p></article>
        <article><h3>Can you work with our developer?</h3><p>Yes. We can diagnose the issue, write the implementation brief, QA the changes and monitor Search Console after release.</p></article>
        <article><h3>How quickly can technical SEO improve results?</h3><p>Critical crawl and indexation fixes can show movement within weeks. Architecture and performance work usually compounds over one to three months.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact Section -->
  <ContactSection />

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</MainLayout>

<style>
/* Technical Icon Grid (used in Hero visual slot) */
.hero-image-container {
  position: relative;
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 500px;
}

.technical-icon-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 2rem;
  padding: 2rem;
}

.tech-icon {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  width: 80px;
  height: 80px;
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
  backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  border-radius: 20px;
  color: white;
  font-size: 2rem;
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
  animation: float 4s ease-in-out infinite;
}

@keyframes float {
  0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0px); }
  50% { transform: translateY(-10px); }
}

.tech-icon:nth-child(odd) {
  animation-delay: 1s;
}

.tech-icon:nth-child(even) {
  animation-delay: 2s;
}

.tech-icon:hover {
  transform: translateY(-5px) scale(1.05);
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
  border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
}

@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .technical-icon-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .technical-icon-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .tech-icon {
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }
}

/* NEW Services Section - Reference Image Style */
.services-section-new {
  padding: 5rem 0;
  background: #131627;
}

.services-layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 4rem;
  align-items: start;
}

.services-content h2 {
  font-size: 2.5rem;
  font-weight: 800;
  color: #ffffff;
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.services-content h2 span {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f0622a, #d4510e);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  background-clip: text;
}

.service-list {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1.5rem;
}

.service-item {
  background: #0d0f1a;
  border-left: 4px solid #f0622a;
  padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
  border-radius: 8px;
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.service-item:hover {
  background: #1a1e32;
  transform: translateX(5px);
}

.service-item h3 {
  font-size: 1.125rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #ffffff;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.service-item p {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: #ffffff;
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin: 0;
}

.services-visual {
  position: sticky;
  top: 2rem;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  min-height: 400px;
}

.visual-card {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(240, 98, 42, 0.05), rgba(255, 107, 53, 0.05));
  border-radius: 20px;
  padding: 3rem 2rem;
  text-align: center;
  border: 1px solid rgba(240, 98, 42, 0.2);
  width: 100%;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
}

.visual-icon {
  width: 80px;
  height: 80px;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f0622a, #d4510e);
  border-radius: 50%;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
  color: white;
  font-size: 2rem;
}

.visual-card h3 {
  font-size: 1.25rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #ffffff;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.visual-stat {
  font-size: 4rem;
  font-weight: 900;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f0622a, #d4510e);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  background-clip: text;
  margin: 1rem 0 0.5rem;
  line-height: 1;
}

.visual-label {
  color: #ffffff;
  font-size: 1rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  margin: 0;
}

@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .services-layout {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  .services-visual {
    position: static;
  }
}

/* Process Section */
.process-section {
  padding: 5rem 0;
  background: #0d0f1a;
}

.process-header {
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: 3rem;
}

.process-header h2 {
  font-size: 2.5rem;
  font-weight: 800;
  color: #ffffff;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.process-header h2 span {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f0622a, #d4510e);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  background-clip: text;
}

.process-header p {
  color: #ffffff;
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  max-width: 800px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.process-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 0;
}

.process-box {
  padding: 3rem 2rem;
  text-align: center;
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
}

.process-box:hover {
  transform: translateY(-5px);
  box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  z-index: 10;
}

.process-box.orange-bg {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f0622a, #d4510e);
}

.process-box.orange-bg h3,
.process-box.orange-bg p {
  color: white;
}

.process-box.white-bg {
  background: #131627;
}

.process-box.white-bg h3 {
  color: #ffffff;
}

.process-box.white-bg p {
  color: #ffffff;
}

.process-box-icon {
  width: 80px;
  height: 80px;
  margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  font-size: 2.5rem;
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.process-box.orange-bg .process-box-icon {
  color: white;
}

.process-box.white-bg .process-box-icon {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f0622a, #d4510e);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  background-clip: text;
}

.process-box:hover .process-box-icon {
  transform: scale(1.1);
}

.process-box h3 {
  font-size: 1.25rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.5px;
}

.process-box p {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin: 0;
}

@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .process-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  }
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .process-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
}

/* Benefits Section */
.benefits-section {
  padding: 5rem 0;
  background: #131627;
}

.benefits-header {
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: 3rem;
}

.benefits-header h2 {
  font-size: 2.5rem;
  font-weight: 800;
  color: #ffffff;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.benefits-header h2 span {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f0622a, #d4510e);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  background-clip: text;
}

.benefits-header p {
  color: #ffffff;
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  max-width: 700px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

.benefits-layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.2fr;
  gap: 4rem;
  align-items: center;
}

.benefits-visual {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
}

.benefits-image {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 400px;
  height: 500px;
  object-fit: cover;
  border-radius: 20px;
  box-shadow: 0 10px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
}

.benefits-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  gap: 2rem;
}

.benefit-card {
  background: #131627;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
  text-align: center;
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.benefit-card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-5px);
  box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
}

.benefit-icon {
  width: 70px;
  height: 70px;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f0622a, #d4510e);
  border-radius: 50%;
